abstract: Proposals to link the interest rates for federal student loans to the rate at which banks borrow from the Federal Reserve are misguided but provide a useful analogy, an economist writes.

lead_paragraph: Phillip Swagel is a professor at the School of Public Policy at the University of Maryland and was assistant secretary for economic policy at the Treasury Department from 2006 to 2009.

abstract: Howard Rains, 43, is trying to bring back an old-time style of Texas fiddling that was popular between the Civil War and World War II.
snippet: Howard Rains, 43, is trying to bring back an old-time style of Texas fiddling that was popular between the Civil War and World War II.
lead_paragraph: During the mid-19th and early 20th centuries, a distinctive form of fiddle music emerged in Texas. Known for idiosyncratic timing and phrasing, this style was commonly played with banjos or guitars on front porches or in living rooms, less for show than for social interaction. It reflected the cross-pollination in Texas after the Civil War, with touches of African-American, Appalachian, Cajun, Czech, German, Irish, Mexican, Polish and Scottish musical forms.

abstract: Admiral Wilkinson commanded the Nautilus, the military’s first machine to harness atomic fission for propulsion rather than weaponry.
snippet: Admiral Wilkinson commanded the Nautilus, the military’s first machine to harness atomic fission for propulsion rather than weaponry.
lead_paragraph: Vice Adm. Eugene P. Wilkinson, who commanded the Nautilus, the United States Navy’s first nuclear-powered submarine and the first machine to harness atomic fission for propulsion rather than weaponry, died on Thursday in Del Mar, Calif. He was 94.

abstract: Two teenagers spend a summer negotiating jobs, friendships and boys.
snippet: Two teenagers spend a summer negotiating jobs, friendships and boys.
lead_paragraph: Summer is here, and with it the search for the perfect beach book, a pithy, plotty page turner that can be discussed with confidence at any cookout or party since everyone seems to be reading the same thing. Best of all is stretching out on the sand with a beach book that is actually set at the shore; somehow it heightens our delight in the transient joy of summer. Sarah Dessen, a seasoned young adult author, and the bold newcomer Leila Howland present readers with two different visions of sun and surf. While each features a young woman struggling to make the right decisions about life and love, one reads as smoothly as a rowboat ride across Central Park Lake while the other tumbles you like a rolling Coney Island wave.

snippet: Bike-sharing program creates a parade of shoes across New York City.
lead_paragraph: On a recent afternoon, Jocelyn Steiber zipped across Prince Street on a bright blue Citi Bike: blond hair loose, floral print Ella Moss sundress parachuting like Marilyn Monroe.

abstract: Cardinal Dolan and other Catholic leaders have responded to the abuse crisis the way the cunning chieftains of a corporation might.
snippet: Cardinal Dolan and other Catholic leaders have responded to the abuse crisis the way the cunning chieftains of a corporation might.
lead_paragraph: BOSTON, Philadelphia, Los Angeles. The archdioceses change but the overarching story line doesn’t, and last week Milwaukee had a turn in the spotlight, with the release of roughly 6,000 pages of records detailing decades of child sexual abuse by Roman Catholic priests there, a sweeping, searing encyclopedia of crime and insufficient punishment.
